cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV 

This paper deals with the use of machine learning to add reactivity to robot behavior, specifically in the domain of obstacle avoidance for robot manipulation. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) as well as machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of dynamic movement primitives (DMPs) and neural networks also suggests a possible connection to control systems (cs.SY) and computer vision (cs.CV) for sensory input.
